### Bug description

This issue is identical to  which was closed as part of milestone 10.0.4. It still occurs with EF Core 10.0.5, and with commit 1a7876ae5f3a8a7cf073214862813f3ff662c5a5.

The [fix commit](https://github.com/dotnet/efcore/commit/c214374f16d2d76932ece40d4b31b257691c4d70) modified `SnapshotModelProcessor`, but running the [repro program](https://github.com/markwijnen/EfCorePendingModelChangesIssue) with .NET Object Allocation Tracking shows 0 instances of `SnapshotModelProcessor` instantiated. Just to be sure, breakpoints in the `SnapshotModelProcessor` constructor or `Process` method do not get hit either.

